definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  (S)-malate -eq- fumarate + H(2)O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  4-fumarylacetoacetate + H(2)O -eq- acetoacetate + fumarate + H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-galactose + ATP -eq- alpha-D-galactose 1-phosphate + ADP + 2 H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-galactosyl-N-acylsphingosine + H2O -eq- D-galactose + N-acylsphingosine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  geranyl diphosphate + isopentenyl diphosphate -eq- 2-trans,6-trans-farnesyl diphosphate + diphosphate.
Catalysis of the successive hydrolysis of beta-D-glucose units from the non-reducing ends of (1--gt-3)-beta-D-glucans, releasing alpha-glucose.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of terminal (1--gt-4)-linked alpha-D-glucose residues successively from non-reducing ends of the chains with release of beta-D-glucose.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + D-glucose -eq- ADP + D-glucose-6-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-glucono-1,5-lactone + H2O -eq- D-gluconate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-glucosamine 6-phosphate + H(2)O -eq- beta-D-fructose 6-phosphate + NH(4)(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-glucosamine 6-phosphate + acetyl-CoA -eq- N-acetyl-D-glucosamine 6-phosphate + CoA + H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-glucose + acceptor -eq- D-glucono-1,5-lactone + reduced acceptor.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-glucose 6-phosphate + NADP+ -eq- D-glucono-1,5-lactone 6-phosphate + NADPH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-glucopyranose 6-phosphate + H2O -eq- D-glucose + phosphate. D-glucopyranose is also known as D-glucose 6-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-glucose 6-phosphate -eq- D-fructose 6-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-glucosyl-N-acylsphingosine + H2O -eq- D-glucose + N-acylsphingosine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-glutamate + ATP -eq- L-glutamyl 5-phosphate + ADP + H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-glutamate 5-semialdehyde + NADP(+) + phosphate -eq- L-glutamyl 5-phosphate + H(+) + NADPH.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-glutamate -eq- 4-aminobutanoate + CO2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-glutamate + H2O + NAD+ -eq- 2-oxoglutarate + NH3 + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-glutamate + H2O + NAD(P)+ -eq- 2-oxoglutarate + NH3 + NAD(P)H + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-glutamate + H2O + NADP+ -eq- 2-oxoglutarate + NH3 + NADPH + H+.

Catalysis of the reaction -  2 L-glutamate + NADP(+) -eq- 2-oxoglutarate + L-glutamine + H(+) + NADPH. This is a two-step reaction -  (a) L-glutamate + NH3 -eq- L-glutamine + H2O, (b) L-glutamate + NADP+ + H2O -eq- NH3 + 2-oxoglutarate + NADPH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-glutamate + ATP + NH(4)(+) -eq- L-glutamine + ADP + 2 H(+) + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-cysteine + L-glutamate + ATP -eq- L-gamma-glutamyl-L-cysteine + ADP + 2 H(+) + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N(2)-acetyl-L-ornithine + L-glutamate -eq- N-acetyl-L-glutamate + L-ornithine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-glutamine + H2O -eq- L-glutamate + NH3.
Catalysis of the reaction -  beta-D-fructose 6-phosphate + L-glutamine -eq- D-glucosamine 6-phosphate + L-glutamate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  glutaryl-CoA + acceptor -eq- crotonoyl-CoA + CO2 + reduced acceptor.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2 glutathione + NADP+ -eq- glutathione disulfide + NADPH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L-gamma-glutamyl-L-cysteine + ATP + glycine -eq- ADP + glutathione + 2 H(+) + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  R-X + glutathione -eq- H-X + R-S-glutathione. R may be an aliphatic, aromatic or heterocyclic group -  X may be a sulfate, nitrile or halide group.
Catalysis of the reaction -  D-glyceraldehyde 3-phosphate + phosphate + NAD+ -eq- 3-phospho-D-glyceroyl phosphate + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acyl-CoA + sn-glycerol 3-phosphate -eq- CoA + 1-acyl-sn-glycerol 3-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  sn-glycerol 3-phosphate + NAD+ -eq- glycerone phosphate + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  sn-glycerol 3-phosphate + a quinone -eq- glycerone phosphate + a quinol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  sn-glycerol 3-phosphate + O(2) -eq- glycerone phosphate + H(2)O(2).
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + glycerol -eq- sn-glycerol 3-phosphate + ADP + 2 H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + glycerone -eq- ADP + glycerone phosphate + 2 H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  5,10-methylenetetrahydrofolate + glycine + H2O -eq- tetrahydrofolate + L-serine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-glucose + (1,4)-alpha-D-glucosyl(n) -eq- UDP + (1,4)-alpha-D-glucosyl(n+1).
Catalysis of the reaction -  glycine + lipoylprotein -eq- S-aminomethyldihydrolipoylprotein + CO2.
Catalysis of the transfer of an alpha-D-mannosyl residue from GDP-mannose into lipid-linked oligosaccharide, forming an alpha-D-mannosyl-D-mannose linkage.

Catalysis of the reaction -  an alpha-D-Man-(1--gt-3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1--gt-6)]-beta-D-Man-(1--gt-4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1--gt-4)-D-GlcNAc-diphosphodolichol + 2 GDP-alpha-D-mannose -eq- an alpha-D-Man-(1--gt-2)-alpha-D-Man-(1--gt-2)-alpha-D-Man-(1--gt-3)-[alpha-D-Man-(1--gt-6)]-beta-D-Man-(1--gt-4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1--gt-4)-D-GlcNAc-diphosphodolichol + 2 GDP + 2 H+. This reaction is the transfer of an alpha-D-mannosyl residue from GDP-mannose into lipid-linked oligosaccharide, forming an alpha-(1--gt-2)-D-mannosyl-D-mannose linkage.

Catalysis of the reaction -  beta-D-Man-(1--gt-4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1--gt-4)-D-GlcNAc-diphosphodolichol + GDP-alpha-D-mannose -eq- alpha-D-Man-(1--gt-3)-beta-D-Man-(1--gt-4)-beta-D-GlcNAc-(1--gt-4)-D-GlcNAc-diphosphodolichol + GDP + H+. This reaction is the transfer of an alpha-D-mannosyl residue from GDP-mannose into lipid-linked oligosaccharide, forming an alpha-(1--gt-3)-D-mannosyl-D-mannose linkage.
Catalysis of the reaction -  tetradecanoyl-CoA + glycyl-peptide -eq- CoA + N-tetradecanoylglycyl-peptide.

Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-N-acetyl-D-galactosamine + glycoprotein-alpha-L-fucosyl-(1,2)-D-galactose -eq- UDP + glycoprotein-N-acetyl-alpha-D-galactosaminyl-(1,3)-(alpha-L-fucosyl-(1,2))-D-galactose.
Catalysis of the reaction -  UDP-galactose + glycoprotein-alpha-L-fucosyl-(1,2)-D-galactose -eq- UDP + glycoprotein-alpha-D-galactosyl-(1,3)-(alpha-L-fucosyl-(1,2))-D-galactose.
Catalysis of the reaction -  GDP + H2O -eq- GMP + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  GTP -eq- 3',5'-cyclic GMP + diphosphate.
